title: Question 2
prompt: Based on the table, which of the following statements is true?
description: Click the <u>one best answer</u> to each question.
feedback: On the chart, three countries have very low numbers of elections, and they all have very different turnouts, ranging from 85% to 51%. Sweden and Czech Republic have nearly the same turnout, and they have the highest and lowest number of elections. Switzerland and Costa Rica also have the same number of elections, and very different turnouts. The chart doesn’t seem to show a relationship between number of elections and turnout.
